						               													<description>In this game, players are pushing their luck and trying to find the exact right combination of fillings in their pie and serving it up.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The active player draws and rolls 2 more dice than the number of players from a bag with 10 dice (8 dice in 4 colors which represent the 4 different pies and 2 wild dice). &amp;#10;Then he takes 1 of the rolled dice and marks the colored number of the dice or the corresponding amount of tiles of that colored pie on the player sheet (each pie has 8 tiles).&amp;#10;After the active player, the other players clockwise take 1 die until every player has selected 1 die. Then the next player becomes the active player and starts a new round with new drawn dice.&amp;#10;There are some (one-time) actions to influence the dice rolls and results like change the the chosen die value +1/-1, add a die from the bag and reroll.&amp;#10;The game ends when one player completed all 4 pies or all 6 colored numbers of 1 pie on the player sheet.&amp;#10;Scoring is done by sum up the marked numbers of the pies, which give points influenced by the pie completeness, and the player with the highest point total wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Solo mode is mostly played the same way, but has an additional end-game trigger when none of the 3 rolled dice can be used to mark a number or pie tiles.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
